---
---

<section id="contributing" class="px-6 py-24 lg:py-32">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl">
    <div class="mb-16 text-center">
      <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-medium tracking-widest uppercase text-accent">
        The Interface
      </p>
      <h2 class="mb-6 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        Every resource is a file.<br />No SDK required.
      </h2>
      <p class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-lg text-text-muted">
        InferNode exposes everything&mdash;LLMs, sensors, databases, agents&mdash;as
        files through the 9P protocol. That single architectural choice eliminates
        entire categories of integration complexity. No client libraries. No API
        wrappers. Just standard file operations.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Language examples -->
    <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">

      <!-- Go 9P server -->
      <div class="min-w-0 rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface overflow-hidden">
        <div class="border-b border-border px-4 py-2 flex items-center justify-between">
          <span class="text-xs font-medium text-node-jetson">Go</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-text-muted italic">9P server — runs on host</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 font-mono text-xs leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto">
          <div class="text-text-muted">// Expose an LLM as a filesystem</div>
          <div><span class="text-node-cloud">func</span> (s *LLMSrv) <span class="text-text">Read</span>(fid *p9p.Fid) {</div>
          <div class="pl-4"><span class="text-node-cloud">if</span> fid.Path == <span class="text-node-jetson">"response"</span> {</div>
          <div class="pl-8">fid.Write(s.llm.Complete(s.prompt))</div>
          <div class="pl-4">}</div>
          <div>}</div>
          <div class="mt-2 text-text-muted">// mount tcp!host!564 /n/llm</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Python 9P server -->
      <div class="min-w-0 rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface overflow-hidden">
        <div class="border-b border-border px-4 py-2 flex items-center justify-between">
          <span class="text-xs font-medium text-node-llm">Python</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-text-muted italic">9P server — runs on host</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 font-mono text-xs leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto">
          <div class="text-text-muted"># Expose a sensor feed as a file</div>
          <div><span class="text-node-cloud">class</span> <span class="text-text">SensorServer</span>(p9p.Server):</div>
          <div class="pl-4"><span class="text-node-cloud">def</span> <span class="text-text">read</span>(self, path, n, off):</div>
          <div class="pl-8"><span class="text-node-cloud">return</span> sensor.read().encode()</div>
          <div class="mt-2 text-text-muted"># mount tcp!pi!564 /n/sensors</div>
          <div class="mt-2 text-text-muted"># Any language. Zero InferNode SDK.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- rc shell inside InferNode -->
      <div class="min-w-0 rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface overflow-hidden">
        <div class="border-b border-border px-4 py-2 flex items-center justify-between">
          <span class="text-xs font-medium text-accent">rc</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-text-muted italic">inside InferNode</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 font-mono text-xs leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto">
          <div class="text-text-muted"># Mount external services</div>
          <div><span class="text-node-laptop">mount</span> tcp!llm-host!564 /n/llm</div>
          <div><span class="text-node-laptop">mount</span> tcp!pi!564 /n/sensors</div>
          <div class="mt-2 text-text-muted"># Use them — just files</div>
          <div><span class="text-node-laptop">echo</span> <span class="text-node-jetson">'summarise'</span> &gt;/n/llm/0/ask</div>
          <div><span class="text-node-laptop">cat</span> /n/llm/0/response</div>
          <div><span class="text-node-laptop">cat</span> /n/sensors/temperature</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The point -->
    <div class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-3xl rounded-xl border border-border bg-bg-surface p-8">
      <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div>
          <h3 class="mb-3 font-semibold">One protocol. Any language.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Inside InferNode, every resource is a file&mdash;you interact with LLMs, sensors,
            and agents using <code class="text-accent font-mono text-xs">open()</code>,
            <code class="text-accent font-mono text-xs">read()</code>,
            <code class="text-accent font-mono text-xs">write()</code>. From the outside,
            any language that speaks
            <a href="https://9p.io/sys/man/5/INDEX.html" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-glow transition" target="_blank" rel="noopener">9P</a>&mdash;a
            simple, open protocol&mdash;can connect to InferNode and work with its resources
            directly. No vendor SDK. No API wrapper. Just a well-documented protocol and
            the language you already know.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="mb-3 font-semibold">Build a service. It becomes native.</h3>
          <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            Write a service in any language. Expose it via 9P. It becomes a file in the
            namespace&mdash;indistinguishable from a built-in resource. Other agents, tools,
            and users can mount and use it immediately. The filesystem is the universal contract.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="mt-10 text-center">
      <a
        href="https://github.com/NERVsystems/infernode"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg border border-border px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-text-muted transition hover:border-accent hover:text-text"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
      >
        Explore the source on GitHub &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
